<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Dartenor</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-11 17:10:31</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The AoF is one hell of a pain camp. The spawn is like this. 20 min spawn for the PHer (champion judicator justicator)and 22 mins for the AoF. I have camped this spawn a ridiculous amount of times. Sometimes he will spawn several times within a 3-4 hour period sometimes he won't spawn once. It all depends on that damn spawn machine *kicks the damn thing several times for good measure*. But seriously this is a highly sought after camp making it hard to get into a group. On our server (Quellious) this chestguard goes for 2500+pp value, yes you heard it right. I myself had to shell out 3k in items just to convince the person to sell it to me and not the other 10 people begging to buy it from her. It's a very nice piece of equipment which is rare and the AoF room is VERY tough to camp. When you account for breaking the room dealing with healers in the upper pool (that will bite you in the ass if you are lucky enough to be fighting an Avatar)the fact that runners are a death/evac wish you start to get the point of why this is a hard room. But when done correctly this is as someone else said one of the best fights in the game. When you see his ugly hairy ass just chilling in that big green bubble you definitely feel the adrenaline pumping. He's very magic resistant and deals out a great amount of damage. So be ready for a fight. Also one thing i forgot to mention is that part of the problem with the aof is that if he gets trained to zone he gets stuck inside of the zone requiring a gm to come and kill him... yep you guessed right no one gets his loot. :( just a sidenote if you notice that the aof hasn't spawned in some time this could be the case but usually when this occurs no phers spawn. Peace out, word to Cazic's mom</font></td></tr></table>
