<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Merribelle</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-15 05:38:19</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Having camped various rooms in Cazic in the last few weeks, including the Avatar room, I thought it might be good to post a few things I learned about the avatar and his nasty little hench-lizards =)<BR>
<BR>
The avvy himself and his placeholder spawn on a 20 minute cycle on the dot; the pool surrounding the bubble spawns four more lizards, and then the Cenobyte / placeholder spawns around the centre of the bubble. You also get wandering spawns down from the planks, and occasional room spawns, usually judicators / justicars. Each spawn cycles in 20minutes, so if you note down when they pop you can easily predict / avoid / delay spawns to split the room up nicelyl this makes it FAR easier to hold the room.<BR>
<BR>
Unlike some people seem to think, you don't need a full group of 35+ players to hold it. A good diverse group of no lower than 29 and no higher than 36 can hold it easily. There are only a few requirements: A cleric is a must, for the HP and AC buffs and heals; a tank, or someone with a ton of HP, and a chanter or bard to mez and charm multiple spawns.<BR>
<BR>
The reason why you need a tank or high HP character is because of the nasty little thing the Avatar does when you tick him off. I discovered he doesn't like being backstabbed for 115 when he turned around and laid a 500pt harm touch on me. He only has one, but he certainly does use it. If I hadn't been at full health, my corpse would still be on the floor down there =)<BR>
<BR>
The most important thing about camping the avatar room is never to panic. Getting upset / worried about when things pop is bad, because that is one tough room to get out of in a hurry. If the pool spawns aren't clear you have to swim out through them, up through the bubble, or make it through the hellish maze of fanatics, zealots and gators that inhabit the planks. Having a druid for buffs / evac / sow is always a good idea just in case things go sour.<BR>
<BR>
My group (a cleric, a necro, a warrior, a paladin, a shaman and myself, a 30 rogue) camped the Avatar room the other day for nearly 5 hours; we killed the avatar 5 times for 1 Raven CG and 4 claws. Unfortunately for me, My group decided to roll for the CG, and I lost... so if you're selling one on Bristlebane at a reasonable price, give me a tell!<BR>
<BR>
Merribelle Stealshearts<BR>
Member of the Hundred Companions<BR>
Rogue of the 31st Shadow<BR>
Daughter of Bristlebane</font></td></tr></table>
